are slow to start or requeued from picking up local changes

Fixing deadlock when command prints a lot to stderr (#1609)

* Fixing deadlock when command prints a lot to stderr

Currently, only stdout is read on the fly. If the stderr pipe fills up,
then, the subprocess will deadlock when trying to write to stderr.
As the parent process, only reads to stdout, and waits for the process
to finish, this will never resolve. This uses instead the select
function to find which file descriptor can be read from.

Add helper class to facilitate PyTorch distributed initialization (#1703)

It is not as straightforward as it could be to initialize PyTorch distributed in a job scheduled with submitit. These changes introduce a helper class that maps the relevant job environment properties and export them as environment variables to easily setup PyTorch distributed with the (default) env:// initialization method.

Tested on a toy job (included as a complete example).
